               <head>Translation of Suhravardi’s ‘Avarif al-ma‘arif</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Miṣbāḥ al-hidāyah va miftāḥ al-kafāyah by ʿIzz al-Dīn Maḥmūd ibn ʿAlī al-Kāshī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh90000334 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85109389" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_979-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="viaf_66318696">ʿIzz al-Dīn Maḥmūd ibn ʿAlī al-Kāshī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="viaf_66318696">عزّ الدّين محمود ابن على الكاشى </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21809">Miṣbāḥ al-hidāyah va miftāḥ al-kafāyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21809">مصباح الهداية و مفتاح الكفاية</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Abridged Persian translation of the comprehensive Arabic treatise on the doctrines and practices of Sufism, the <title>ʿAvārif al-maʿārif</title> of <persName key="person_f7609" role="ant">Shihāb al-Dīn ʿUmar ibn Muḥammad al-Suhravardī</persName> (d. 632/1234), by a student, <persName key="viaf_66318696" role="trl">ʿIzz al-Dīn Maḥmūd ibn ʿAlī al-Kāshī</persName> (d. 735/1334-5). 
                        </p>
                        <p>The passage naming the author is missing from this volume. 
</p>
                        <p>At least 14 leaves have been lost after folio 2. 
</p>
                        <p>With the exception of the first bāb, which this volume lacks, the work is divided into ten bāb. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. <persName key="viaf_79056967" role="cataloguer">Arberry</persName> dates the manuscript to within the translator’s lifetime and attributes annotations and corrections in the margin to the author’s hand, on the basis of a collation note at the end (f. 161r), dated Wednesday, 10 Shavvāl 734/1334. As the manuscript is written in a later form of scribal nastaʿlīq, with a few shikastah-style flourishes, the early dating is less probable, and more likely to date to the early eighteenth century. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Several owner’s notes and seal impressions erased (f. 1r). Surviving note by <persName key="person_f7033" role="asn">ʿAbd al-Raḥmān Chishtī al-ʿAlavī</persName> states the manuscript was presented to a relative of the Timurid or Mughal ruler, <persName key="viaf_6178410" role="oth">Emperor ʿĀlamgīr I</persName>, namely, <persName key="person_f7309" role="fmo">Mīrzā Jaʿfar ibn Zayn al-ʿĀbidīn ibn Āṣaf Khān "Jaʿfar"</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Opening flyleaf has two notes of interest: 1) binder’s name stated as <persName key="person_f7354" role="bnd">Muḥammad Ḥafīẓ the ṣaḥḥāf</persName>; 2) the name of a previous owner, <persName key="person_f7393" role="fmo">Muḥammad Raz̤ī or Murtaz̤á</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Boards of leather binding intact, doublures of polychrome marbled paper; spine missing. 
</p>
                     </note>
